To prepare for the new Modern Warfare i started off with the one that kicked the series into new heights. Bare in mind I played the remaster version. This is a solid game even in today standards. A short but impactful campaign that has good Characters  great set pieces and tight gameplay. In terms of arcade action you can't get any better then this. The multiplayer is as good as it's always been with the creating a class and adding attachments and skins. There are problems of course. First off the loot box system is horrible. I hate it and screw Activision for putting it in here and screw them harder for making dlc maps for a remaster...dlc. Activision really don't care. And for me I played it through veteran and I get it. It's hardest difficulty but you do sometimes feel really unfair. I lost count how many times I'd fight the same enemy after a checkpoint restart and it always be random if I'd have time to shoot him or he'd snap to me and kill me quicker then I can aim down sight's. Our felt very unfair. Apart from that the game is great and set in stone a series that would make way for a generation of gamers. But what did you guys and gals think? Let me know and I'll see you guys... In the next post.  #game #Games #gaming #videogame #videogames #callofduty #callofduty4modernwarfare #callofduty4remastered

This is a real photo of Bruce McCandless floating untethered in space.â €In this Feb. 7  1984 photograph taken by his fellow crewmembers aboard the Earth-orbiting Space Shuttle Challenger on the STS-41B mission  NASA astronaut Bruce McCandless II approaches his maximum distance from the vehicle. McCandless became the first astronaut to maneuver about in space untethered  during this first "field" tryout of a nitrogen-propelled  hand-controlled backpack device called the Manned Maneuvering Unit (MMU).â €For 50 years  NASA has been "suiting up" for spacewalking. The first American to conduct a spacewalk  astronaut Edward H. White II  floated into the vastness of space on the Gemini IV mission on June 3  1965. For more than 20 minutes  White maneuvered himself around the Gemini spacecraft as it traveled from over Hawaii to the Gulf of Mexico--making his orbital stroll 6 500 miles long. At the end of the 20-minute spacewalk  White was exuberant. "This is the greatest experience " he said. "It's just tremendous."â €Since this historic first  NASA astronauts have performed spacewalks  or extravehicular activity (EVA) in NASA-speak  on the Gemini  Apollo  Skylab  Space Shuttle and International Space Station programs. Astronauts have explored the lunar surface  completed 82 spacewalks outside of the space shuttle  and 187 spacewalks  to date  outside the International Space Station. A total of 166 hours of spacewalks were carried out to service the Hubble Space Telescope. Today  NASA is developing new advanced spacesuits for use by astronauts as they travel to new deep-space locations on the journey to Mars. The next-generation suit will incorporate a number of technology advances to shorten preparation time  improve safety and boost astronaut capabilities during spacewalks and surface activities.â €Via NASA#universe_dop #toptorontotech #technology #tech2019 #technews #shotoniphone #huaweip30pro #huaweicanada #pixel4 #techreviews #science #tech #Toronto #space #STEM #computers #gaming #gamers  CREDIT: @universe_dope@TopTechToronto: Your Tech ğŸ”Œ â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€” â£ Follow @TopTechToronto â£ â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â£

Gun Brothers First Look Android Gameplay ( September 2019 )  The Top Commando is an action platformer that sees you playing one of a number of gun-toting characters. There are different classes  and you'll unlock more as you play along. Whoever you're playing as though  the idea is the same - shoot everything and don't get shot.  You get crates when you complete missions  and inside of those you'll find new gear. Stick it on your team and they'll get tougher  getting them ready for the difficulties ahead. You'll need to upgrade them as well  using dog tags that you're rewarded as you fight.  Different enemies have different patterns of attack  which is great when you're fighting them one on one  but once there's more than a few on the screen you're going to be jumping and running your way through storms of bullets from every angle. Finally it's #backlogbattler time and this time it's Fist of the North Star Lost Paradise on PS4. A game where you play as Kenshiro in another non canon adventure where knowing characters does help. In the tutorial you take out Shin  then go to the city of Eden where you become it's protector. You befriend the captain of the guard  get a truck you can ride around the sandbox in  do odd jobs like bartending  healing and managing a host club. You get random battles with goons everywhere which build up exp. You get references to the anime and manga everywhere. It's a wander around fighty drivey smash people's skulls in affair that plays a lot like Yakuza. It's mindless and can rack up the time easily. It's a fun game and if you like the series you'll love it. If you allow things to get on top of you however the main story will take a back seat and you'll find yourself just wandering around or driving around the desert looking for people to kill and items to get in the wastes. Pasalnya permainan berjenis battle royale ini merupakan perpindahan dari versi PC. Tak ayal spesifikasi yang dibutuhkan juga harus tinggi seperti platform iOS versi 11.  Perbedaan tidak dari spesifikasi saja  melainkan juga kemudahan akses. PUBG lebih mudah didapatkan para gamers melalui aplikasi Google Playstore. Sementara pengembang Fortnite memutuskan untuk tidak menawarkan game buatannya di aplikasi itu karena akan mendapat potongan keuntungan sebesar 30 persen.  Pengguna yang terbilang banyak  tak ayal membuat PUBG bisa meraih keuntungan besar sepanjang tahun ini yakni sebanyak 860 juta dollar (Rp12 triliun). Review Summary- Control ===================== SCORE: 9.1 ===================== You looking for a paranormal  sci-fi action game? This is the game for you! I can guarantee you haven't played anything quite like this before.  It has such a unique style and atmosphere  it oozes mystique  and has a certain stillness that keeps you on edge. It's reminiscent of the old Stanley Kubrick classics  so it wouldn't surprise me if that's where they got their inspiration from.  The combat is some of the most fun you'll have this year. Both the gunplay and psychic abilities are polished and each battle is a thrill. You'll always leave the battlefield in a state of choas  thanks to the destructible environments.  The story is full of mystery and will keep you invested  even if it can be a bit confusing at times  especially with the in-game terminology. Extra lore is told through an excessive amount of collectibles  so while there is a lot to learn about this fascinating world  you're constantly stopping to read yet again. It disrupts gameplay and I do wish it was handled more efficiently.  The side missions are just as much of a standout as the main story  with each one containing an interesting and unique storyline  and I always looked forward to each one.  Exploration was one of the weaker elements of the game  as it did get a little frustrating at times getting to where you needed to go. But this was made up by the amount of hidden secrets (and even some good puzzles) scattered around each area.  While it's a relatively short game  I still recommend this to anyone  as it's one of the better games this year. On-going review- Control ==================== My last post before I wrap up my review tomorrow. Now I've been mostly positive about this game so far  but it's not perfect  and there were a couple of things that held it back from true greatness.  I already talked about the excessive amounts of collectibles in my last post. It's fine to have a lot of extra lore  but surely there was a more efficient way to go about it.  My other main issue was how useless the map was. Maybe use it as a rough guide  but not to go exactly where you need to go. A lot of areas are multi-story  and the map just shows everything in one clump. If you're trying to get from one room to another  the map be more misleading than anything  and I did get frustrated quite a few times trying to get around.  When you think of maps from other games  like Resident Evil 2  they're laid out so clearly it helps makes exploration more fun because you're not wasting time looking at blank walls where the map says there should a doorway.  But I will admit my criticisms are fairly minor and didn't detract too much from the fun overall. Does anyone else Remember Minecade? Well  if you don't  then I can't say I blame you. Minecade was a server network that was popular in the Java edition of Minecraft for a short while. One of the most popular games on it was Super Craft Bross  which was basically Kit PVP with double jumping and special abilities. Sethbling  a Minecraft YouTuber who specializes in making mechanics and contraptions  was a pretty big face of the server for a while.  However  as time went by  things around the server started to go downhill. Updates for Super Craft Bros. were few and far between. Balancing issues and bugs were rarely if ever  fixed. To make things worse  Minecraft's popularity was in a lull. It was around this time I quit playing on Minecade because the games I liked just weren't fun to play anymore.  Fast forward to now. With Minecraft getting a bit of an extra life when it comes to mainstream popularity  I wondered what Minecade has been up to. Last I checked  they could barely break 50 players  and those players were mostly on a rather basic creative server. When I went to the website  all I found was  well  this. The website is a mess. Iâ€™ve also checked around a few forums and canâ€™t find much.  So. What happened to Minecade? Iâ€™ve been steadily picking at 'Fire Emblem Three Houses' for the past month or so and while I admit I havenâ€™t quite finished the game I can say confidently that it is one of my favorites of the year. While I donâ€™t have a ton of experience with the Fire Emblem series it's hard to imagine the diehards finding too much at fault with itâ€™s core gameplay. The turn based â€œrock paper scissorsâ€ battles the series is iconic for are so engaging and addictive to play and beautifully presented. Thereâ€™s something so epic about having the camera rapidly zoom in to the ground level of the battlefield so you can watch your characters duke it out. But I think the crowning achievement of this game is its story and narrative structure. You play as â€œThe Professorâ€ a sort of blank slate character who finds him or herself teaching at a prestigious military academy. In between battles you will fill your time lecturing and getting to know your students (who of course are your soldiers in battles) all the while completing side quests around the school. Itâ€™s essentially a lighter but more focused version of what the Persona series does. Within the first couple hours of play I found myself really caring for my students and motivated to prepare them as effectively as I could so they wouldnâ€™t die in combat (yes perma-death is still a thing if you want it). This along with a storyline that evolves and twists based on your actions and choices makes for an immensely satisfying narrative experience. Finally it's #backlogbattler time and this time it's Fist of the North Star Lost Paradise on PS4. A game where you play as Kenshiro in another non canon adventure where knowing characters does help. In the tutorial you take out Shin  then go to the city of Eden where you become it's protector. You befriend the captain of the guard  get a truck you can ride around the sandbox in  do odd jobs like bartending  healing and managing a host club. You get random battles with goons everywhere which build up exp. You get references to the anime and manga everywhere. It's a wander around fighty drivey smash people's skulls in affair that plays a lot like Yakuza. It's mindless and can rack up the time easily. It's a fun game and if you like the series you'll love it. If you allow things to get on top of you however the main story will take a back seat and you'll find yourself just wandering around or driving around the desert looking for people to kill and items to get in the wastes. It's a fun game and I think it's worth the Â£30 asking price. #sega #sony #gaming #gamer #retro #arcade #franchise #retrocollectiveeurope #pickups #3d #adventure #rpg #action #3d #atlus #fistofthenorthstar #hokutonoken #kenshiro #playstation #ps4 #gamestergram #videogames #gamersunite #gamecollector #gamersofinstagram #jackrabbitgamer

Pickpocketing is also interesting in this game. You have to get close to a person and while remaing undetected  reach into their pockets.  The timer at the start determines how many seconds you will get to rummage around looking for items. The longer you can hold out the longer you get to look.  As the timer goes up  depending on your skill and your marks various attributes  it gets more dangerous to keep rummaging. The background of the timer will start to turn red when you are close to getting caught.  Once you have completed the timer mini game successfully you use what time you have earned to go through the various items and uncover what they are. You pick what you want and then have to navigate to the exit.  You manage to do that before time runs out and you have successfully pickpocketed someone!  Protip: To level Pickpocketing up faster and easier  do it to people who are sleeping! . . . . . . . . . . #pickpocket #kingdomcomedeliverance #pickpocketing #kingdomcome #medieval #rpg #gaming #videogames #simulation #xboxgamepass #XboxShare #XboxOneX #gamepass #rogue #thief #stealing #ninjaskills

BIONIC COMMANDO: In 1987 arcade gamers became special forces soldiers in order to infiltrate an enemy base and stop the launch of a devastating missile attack.  A classic action platform game from Capcom this is one of the coolest games of its time thanks to all jumping being removed in favour of using an extendable arm to move around the level.  Converted to a ton of home computers including the Amiga  Atari ST  C64  ZX Spectrum and Amstrad CPC this also came to the NES although that version was very different.  Did you ever play this game? Akumajou Dracula X: Chi no Rondo  AKA Castlevania: Rondo of blood.  The game was released in japan on oct 29th  1993. An amazing halloween gift for our Japanese buddies! And it wasn't released outside of Japan for almost 15 years. At some point it was considered the best Castlevania ever  and I think everyone thought alike until Symphony of the Night. So basically  a lost jewell for the western world. There was a remake in the SNES but it was actually a complete different game. It was possible to play it as an unlockable game in The Dracula X Chronicles... But now we are going to be able to enjoy the original game for the first time  on the Turbografx-16 mini!!! So  the first videos are an amazing intro animation. The voice translation is: "Long ago people lived in peace and harmony. No one noticed the looming shadow among them. Their senses clouded in darkness  evil ate away at their souls. In the late hour they congregate to call the powers of Satan with sinful blood to save them from their mortal existence. Evis has once again been made flesh. He can become a bat  fog  or wolf and feasts on human blood. Lord of darkness  master of Castlevania  Dracula walk among us." This game has a fantastic soundtrack  making use of the CD-Rom capacity for better sound quality. There's a 2CD OST released with music from this game and also from Castlevania Bloodlines. Barcode scanning toys and arcade games were extremely popular in the 90's Japan including the Datach Famicom add on  the later Digivices and Barcode Wars by Bandai. The strength of the Barcode Wars series was its connection to nintendo  allowing them to make exclusive barcode games with nintendo franchise such as Mario Bros and Zelda. . It also allowed players connect to their Super Famicom or original Gameboy via the 'Barcode Boy' to send data from the barcode cards into the Barcode Battler console games. . Barcode Battler was highly successful in Japan and even saw a release of western versions with alternative art and characters. . I finished Link's Awakening earlier on today (I dunno about you but you have to 100% everything before you can tackle the final boss  right?!) Just wanted to give my thoughts!  This is absolutely how a remake should be handled. I loved it from start the finish. I remember the art style throwing a few people when it was originally unveiled but I thought it was cute as hell then and thanks to the sound it makes when you dash with the Pegasus Boots I think it's even more cute now ğŸ˜ The soundtrack matches the chibi-esque style perfectly. However. The was one new feature that downright annoyed me... Dampe's dungeon creator. For anyone else who went ahead and completed the Gold Challenges  I have one word. Stairs. Good God. I'm not sure I can do this justice in text but you cannot (as far as I know) manually connect stairs to stairs. This made "Bows > Swords" really frustrating because the damn stairs just wouldn't connect to the ones I wanted them to connect with! It seems to connect stairwells to the ones closest so it's "easy" to work around but I shouldn't have to find a work around ğŸ˜… You could argue this was just an add on and has no real impact on the main game  and you'd be half right... some of the optional collectibles (heart/bottle/seashell) are locked behind Dampe's tutorials. You can also only use preexisting dungeon rooms... Which means you're replaying rooms from previous dungeons over and over again. With a little work and a bit more freedom I'm sure a Zelda Dungeon Creator would make a fantastic little eshop game but as it is now I'd give it little more that a "meh". BUT I DID LOVE THE GAME  HONESTLY. DON'T READ TOO MUCH INTO MY BITCHING ABOUT FUCKING STAIRS ğŸ˜‚  I probably should have started in Hero Mode because with the new addition of bottles the game was waaaaay easier. ------------------------------------------------ . . . . . . . . #retrocollectivena #retrocollectiveeurope #retrocollective #VideoGames #Gamer #retrocollective #retrogames #gamestagram  #instagaming #retro #gaming #collector #retrostyle #retrovideogames #retrocommunity #retrogaming #igersnintendo #zelda #thelegendofzelda #LinksAwakening #link #marin #switch #nintendo #WeekofZelda

To prepare for the new Modern Warfare i started off with the one that kicked the series into new heights. Bare in mind I played the remaster version. This is a solid game even in today standards. A short but impactful campaign that has good Characters  great set pieces and tight gameplay. In terms of arcade action you can't get any better then this. The multiplayer is as good as it's always been with the creating a class and adding attachments and skins. There are problems of course. First off the loot box system is horrible. I hate it and screw Activision for putting it in here and screw them harder for making dlc maps for a remaster...dlc. Activision really don't care. And for me I played it through veteran and I get it. It's hardest difficulty but you do sometimes feel really unfair. I lost count how many times I'd fight the same enemy after a checkpoint restart and it always be random if I'd have time to shoot him or he'd snap to me and kill me quicker then I can aim down sight's. Our felt very unfair. Apart from that the game is great and set in stone a series that would make way for a generation of gamers. But what did you guys and gals think? Let me know and I'll see you guys... In the next post.  #game #Games #gaming #videogame #videogames #callofduty #callofduty4modernwarfare #callofduty4remastered
